properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 28 at 4:10PM AKST until January 30 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blizzard conditions possible. Total snow accumulations of
4 to 8 inches with locally higher amounts possible. Winds could
gust between 45 to 60 mph.

* WHERE...From Portage Valley through Turnagain Pass

* WHEN...From Wednesday afternoon through late Wednesday night.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow will develop tonight and continue
through Wednesday. The snow and winds will increase in
intensity beginning Wednesday afternoon before diminishing late
Wednesday night. Near whiteout conditions are possible from
Portage Valley through Turnagain Pass. Blowing snow could also
reduce visibility to 1/2 mile at times south of Moose Pass.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH IN EFFECT FROM WEDNESDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH LATE WEDNESDAY NIGHT
